detailedReviews.author: Adam Miller
detailedReviews.text:
Ordered six 18" thin crust, 1 topping pizzas for a lunch n' learn event at a customer's office 1.5 miles away from this location. Placed order at 10:15am for noon delivery. Called at 11:15 to ensure noon arrival, was given complete assurance of correct address and time. Called again at 12:05 to check status, was told driver was 10 minutes away (Maps showed transit time was 11 minutes from their location to ours). Called again at 12:35 for an explanation why our lunch was 35 minutes late. I was told literally the same thing, the driver was 10 minutes away. I asked for a conference call with the driver, she said the driver would call me back. He called 5 minutes later and arrived 5 minutes after that with lukewarm pizza, congealed cheese and soft/soggy crust. He also acted irritated when he handed me four of the six pizzas and and I turned to bring them to my group, because he wanted to hand me the other  two pizzas first. If you're curious, I had already pre-tipped $30 on a $200 order.

These people do not care about your business. They embarrassed me in front of important clients and never offered an explanation or apology. Please spend your money elsewhere. You'll be much happier.

EDIT: TJ, the owner, called the next day after my review and apologized profusely for what had happened. He offered to refund or remake the entire order, and seemed sincerely concerned about making things right. I've amended my review from 1 star to 3 stars as a result, hopefully accountability from ownership will result in better experiences for other customers. However, you cannot fix the past.

Be careful when choosing service providers that may hold away over your business relationships. I had to learn that lesson the hard way, courtesy of Rosati's Pizza of Chicago.

detailedReviews.author: Sheena M
detailedReviews.text: Update: I have reached out to the customer service and was told once again I would be contacted by the manager of the location, however I still have not heard anything in regards to trying to resolve the problem/issue. I preordered pizza for my mother's birthday at this location as it was close to my job.  I input the incorrect date for pick up, and was contacted by the restaurant to pick up my pizza. The worker was very rude and belligerent over the phone. I sent someone to pick up the pizzas as I was not in the area at that time. This was my first time visiting this location and it definitely will be my last. The pizza was burned and not edible. I called the restaurant and asked to speak with a manager to explain the issue and was informed the manager wasn't in and would give me a call back. I even informed the staff that I would bring back the pizzas, to which I was told to wait until I was contacted by the manager. It has now been two weeks and still no manager has contacted me in regards to the matter. I have called over three times to speak with a manager and the staff continues to say that the manager is not in and all I get is the run around constantly. My money has gone to waste, $46 down the drain smh. Save yourself the disappointment and visit another location as this one is not it at all. The staff is rude and the pizza is definitely not up to par.

detailedReviews.author: Julian Robertson
detailedReviews.text: I rarely give 5 stars, but I have to show love when it is due. My family and I went in on a late evening and ordered a deep dish for dine in. While we waiting the 30 minutes for it to cook we chatted with the owner. He was a sweet guy who provided our table with some house garlic parm fries (give them a try), and be also gave my son a slice of cheesecake. Enough of the small talk though. THE PIZZA!! Normally I'm not standing around 30 minutes for any dine in food happily, but I would have waiting 3 hours for that pizza knowing what I know now. IF I COULD HAVE ONE PIZZA FOR THE REST OF MY LIFE I'M NOT SURE IF I'D PICK ONE OVER THEIR DEEP DISH. Maybe I'm exaggerating some, but I'll let you be the judge of that.
